==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} [[#Latin|Procyon]], from Greek [[προκύον]] (''prokyuon''), meaning "before the dog", since it precedes the "Dog Star" [[Sirius]].

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Procyon'''

#{{star}}: A [[star]] in the [[constellation]] [[Canis Minor]]; Alpha (α) Canis Minoris. The eighth brightest star in the night sky.

====Translations====
